# <project name> — Claude Guidelines

## Weight class

work-grade. This is serious, multi-phase software with other stakeholders and a long lifespan. Full ceremony earns its keep here. Skills read this section: it selects the full Definition of Done (`mix check`, moduledocs, integration tests) and enables the skeptic design review in `/workflow-kit:promote-design`.

## Stack & commands

Phoenix LiveView, <database>. `mix check` is the verification gate (format, credo, dialyzer, tests). <project-specific commands here>.

Verify command: `mix check` (declare a different command here if this repo's real gate differs — e.g. `mix precommit` — the Definition of Done and phase-close read this line; absent, they default to the command above).

## Document chain

Active initiative: docs/YYYY-MM-DD-<initiative>/ (the document chain lives here; create-prd maintains this line when a new initiative starts). PRD.org, DESIGN.org, PLAN.org, and stories/ are org format, never markdown — conventions in the workflow-kit plugin's `org-conventions` skill. PRD.org is the invariant contract: never edit it (the prd-lock hook enforces this); conflicts with its Success Criteria are surfaced to the human as Amendment questions, and Amendments invalidate downstream artifacts until re-reviewed. DESIGN.org body edits are always paired per the org-conventions two-log rules (Decision Log entry for judgments, Advisory for every post-canon body edit). `docs/superpowers/specs/` holds brainstorm specs — transient, uncommitted territory, gitignored (see `project-setup/.gitignore`); it is never referenced by section number once a document is committed. `docs/learnings.org` is the repo-level lessons file, cumulative across initiatives — never inside an initiative directory; entry rules live in its header (one dated entry per learning; update rather than duplicate; delete entries that prove wrong).

## Workflow

Pipeline: brainstorm (Superpowers) → `/workflow-kit:create-prd` → `/workflow-kit:promote-design` (skeptic review runs at this weight class) → `/workflow-kit:user-stories` → per story: TDD implementation then `/workflow-kit:story-closeout` then `/workflow-kit:update-design` → `/workflow-kit:phase-close`. One story per session, working from the story file's embedded Design excerpt as the source of truth. Out-of-scope discoveries are recorded as Deferred, never fixed inline. Planning artifacts are written in org per the conventions file, even where upstream skill examples show markdown. Consider enabling the optional `stop-test-gate.sh` hook (instructions in the script header) so a red suite can never be left standing.

An implementation session refuses to start work over a dirty working tree; unexplained working-tree state is surfaced to the human, never classified-and-fixed by the session itself. (A session once misattributed and silently deleted the human's uncommitted scratch code — the incident this rule exists to prevent.)
